  "prompt": "My friend block a person on what's app how could I know really he is blocked?",
  "response": "There are a few ways to check if someone has blocked you on WhatsApp:\n\n1. Check profile picture and status:\n- If you can't see their profile picture\n- Their status is no longer visible\n\n2. Message delivery indicators:\n- Only one grey tick (sent) but no blue double ticks\n- Messages remain at single grey tick and never deliver\n\n3. Last seen status:\n- You can't see their \"last seen\" time\n- Their online status disappears\n\n4. Call attempts:\n- Calls don't go through\n- Repeated calls fail to connect\n\n5. Add to group test:\n- Try adding them to a group\n- If you can't add them, they might have blocked you\n\n6. Profile information:\n- Can't view their profile information\n- Profile appears unchanged from last time you saw it\n\nNote: These signs aren't 100% definitive proof of blocking. The person might have privacy settings adjusted or network issues.\n\nRecommended approach:\n- Don't obsess over being blocked\n- Respect the other person's decision\n- Move forward positively",
